body:
So the devs came out and said that they want to add more story and progression in it. so I came up with this on a comment.

&quot;I think more story is an amazing idea, giving conflicts between characters and why there is league of legends will help a lot. giving us more conflicts between characters is a really good strong idea for you because league is about conflict between 2 teams so It would make sense for a narrative to go that way. maybe you should do an event were you implement a game mode that allows people to choose a side (for example demacia and noxian champions) and only allow champions from that line to be picked. the match will start and new objectives on a new map will make it feel more story like, and when 1 side wins that is tallied up for a certain side and the side with the most victory&#039;s progresses the story in that alternative narrative at the end of the game modes set time. that will allow a really cool game mode to come out and the story can be progressed and the community is taking part the entire way. lots of luck for the future and keep being awesome riot.&quot;

This I feel would work really well because the struggle of the player is shared with the story and champions! please leave a comment and vote on the poll to tell me what you think.
